PETER KLEIN:  You know, the thing that I can say is, we have a great product pipeline.
We don't have visibility into exactly what business spend will be, so we're just going to have work through that over the next couple of quarters.
The only thing we can control, as we've been saying, is the products.
We feel like we're executing against those, and we'll keep working the enterprise agreements as we can.
HEATHER BELLINI:  So, would that mean it would be unreasonable to assumeI mean last year, I would imagine, was a difficult closing environment as well, so as a measure of conservatism would kind of seasonal growth rates like you had last year in deferred be prudent in your view versus expecting an up-tick?
PETER KLEIN:  I would just encourage anybody to think through their view, there are differing views of what enterprise spend is going to be.
You'll just have to apply your view of that.
