PETER KLEIN:  Yes.
Thanks, Kash.
Good question.
On the consumer side, we had a very good retail quarter, about $500 million, which is a little bit more than we expected.
So, that dynamic that you highlighted is actually happening.
People are going to retail and buying shrink-wrapped Windows to put on their PCs.
On the business side, anecdotally, a lot of interest.
