Business revenue grew 9 percent, and within that multi-year licensing revenue grew 12 percent, and transactional revenue grew 2 percent driven by higher attach worldwide.
Consumer revenue declined 4 percent reflecting consumer PC dynamics in developed markets, which was partially offset by higher attach rates.
We saw strong growth in our productivity server offerings with Exchange, SharePoint, and Lync collectively growing double digits this quarter.
CIOs continue to invest in our application roadmap, and new productivity scenarios.
