SATYA NADELLA:  Yes, two things, Mark.
One is the diversity of products that Microsoft has from silicon tape out to services that we are continuously updating in Azure, or Office 365, is a lot more than let's say when we first created the Microsoft engineering system.
That was for retail packaged product.
So since then a lot has changed and a lot has evolved.
And, so what we are doing is we are introducing new functions and new skills, design is even more important than it ever was.
Data analytics, as you said, is very important to us.
And, they're not outside functions.
They're functions that are integral to how we do product development, how we do A/B testing, how we do log analysis on a continuous basis.
So, that's the engineering process and culture change that we have ongoing and in fact a lot of learning from a variety of different teams that's now spreading across a lot of Microsoft.
MARK MOERDLER:  And, Amy, one quick question, we saw a significant acceleration this quarter in cloud revenue.
I guess Amy or Satya.
